---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

export const meta = {
  title: "VYM Dividend Analysis & History",
  description: "Dive into VYM's latest dividend yield, rock-solid history, and expense ratios. Could this Vanguard ETF be the ultimate anchor for a 2026 income portfolio?",
  category: "tool",
  published: "2026-03-15",
};

const schema = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "VYM Dividend Analysis & History",
    "description": meta.description,
    "datePublished": meta.published,
    "author": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "Westmount Fundamentals"
    }
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the vym dividend?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "The VYM dividend is a quarterly distribution paid to shareholders, derived from the Vanguard High Dividend Yield ETF's holdings of primarily U.S. companies characterized by higher-than-average dividend yields."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the vym dividend yield?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Currently, the VYM dividend yield sits at approximately 2.26%, offering a compelling premium over broad market index funds while maintaining a conservative risk profile."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the vym dividend history?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "VYM has a robust dividend history of consistent growth. Annual payouts have grown from $3.10 per share in 2021 to over $3.50 per share in 2025."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the projected vym dividend yield 2025?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "The final VYM dividend yield for 2025 normalized around 2.26%, reflecting steady corporate earnings among value-oriented companies despite shifting interest rates."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the forecasted vym dividend yield 2026?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "While exact figures depend on ongoing market performance and dividend declarations, analysts anticipate the VYM dividend yield in 2026 will maintain a competitive baseline near the 2.5% to 3.0% range assuming stable price appreciation."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
];
---
<SiteLayout site="westmount" title={meta.title} description={meta.description} canonical="https://westmountfundamentals.com/vym-dividend" schema={schema}>
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="hero">
      <h1>VYM Dividend Analysis & History</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Vanguard's premier high-dividend yield tracking fund</p>
    </div>

    <section>
      <h2>VYM Overview & Key Metrics</h2>
      <p>The <strong>Vanguard High Dividend Yield ETF (VYM)</strong> is specifically engineered to track the performance of companies that pay dividends that are generally higher than average. For investors constructing a conservative, income-focused portfolio, the <strong>vym dividend</strong> acts as a foundational block, providing both reliable cash flow and a history of moderate capital appreciation.</p>

      <p>As a Vanguard product, VYM boasts an incredibly low expense ratio, ensuring that almost all of the generated income is passed directly through to the shareholder. Its portfolio skews heavily toward Large Value companies, including established names in the Financials, Industrials, and Consumer Defensive sectors.</p>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Current Snapshot</h3>
        <table>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <th>Current Dividend Yield</th>
              <td>2.26%</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th>Price-to-Earnings (P/E) Ratio</th>
              <td>20.77</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th>Assets Under Management (AUM)</th>
              <td>$92.32 Billion</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th>Category</th>
              <td>Large Value</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th>Payout Frequency</th>
              <td>Quarterly</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <p>At 2.26%, the <strong>vym dividend yield</strong> offers a meaningful premium over the <a href="/spy-dividend">SPY dividend yield</a> (1.06%), satisfying income investors without stepping into riskier, high-yield derivative products.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>VYM Dividend History & Growth Trends</h2>
      <p>Examining the <strong>vym dividend history</strong> showcases Vanguard's success in selecting robust, dividend-growing companies. Even during periods of economic uncertainty, VYM has managed to sustain and grow its aggregate payout, proving the resilience of value-oriented, cash-flowing enterprises.</p>

      <div class="card">
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Year</th>
              <th>Total Annual Payout (per share)</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>2021</td>
              <td>$3.10</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>2022</td>
              <td>$3.25</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>2023</td>
              <td>$3.48</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>2024</td>
              <td>$3.50</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>2025</td>
              <td>$3.50</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <p>Throughout the <strong>vym dividend yield 2025</strong> cycle, payouts stabilized as corporations balanced returning cash to shareholders with internal investment in a shifting rate environment. As we look ahead to the <strong>vym dividend yield 2026</strong>, moderate but consistent low-single-digit percentage growth in the raw dividend payout is largely anticipated by analysts.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Dividend Reinvestment (DRIP) Calculator</h2>
      <p>How much passive income can a portfolio of VYM generate? Use our interactive calculator below to model your quarterly and annual income stream. By opting into a DRIP (Dividend Reinvestment Plan), you compound your shares automatically, allowing your income to snowball over time.</p>

      <div class="card calculator-container">
        <h3>Project Your VYM Income</h3>
        <div style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">
          <label for="sharesInput" style="display:block; margin-bottom:0.5rem; font-weight:bold;">Shares Owned:</label>
          <input type="number" id="sharesInput" value="100" min="1" style="width:100%; padding:0.75rem; border-radius:6px; border:1px solid var(--border-color); background:var(--bg-color); color:var(--text-primary);">
        </div>
        <div style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">
          <label for="priceInput" style="display:block; margin-bottom:0.5rem; font-weight:bold;">Current Price per Share ($):</label>
          <input type="number" id="priceInput" value="120.00" step="0.01" style="width:100%; padding:0.75rem; border-radius:6px; border:1px solid var(--border-color); background:var(--bg-color); color:var(--text-primary);">
        </div>
        <button id="calcBtn" style="background:var(--accent-color); color:#fff; border:none; padding:0.75rem 1.5rem; border-radius:6px; font-weight:bold; cursor:pointer; width:100%;">Calculate Annual Income</button>

        <div id="calcResults" style="margin-top: 1.5rem; display:none; padding:1rem; background:var(--bg-color); border-radius:6px; border:1px solid var(--border-color);">
          <p style="margin:0 0 0.5rem 0;">Estimated Annual Income (No Reinvestment): <strong id="resNoDrip" style="color:var(--accent-color); font-size:1.2rem;">$0.00</strong></p>
          <p style="margin:0;">Estimated Annual Income (With DRIP): <strong id="resDrip" style="color:var(--accent-color); font-size:1.2rem;">$0.00</strong></p>
          <p style="font-size:0.8rem; color:var(--text-secondary); margin-top:0.5rem;">*Assumes a static 2.26% yield and constant share price over the next year.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Comparison to Category Average</h2>
      <p>Within the Large Value category, VYM frequently competes with other popular dividend ETFs like Schwab's US Dividend Equity ETF (SCHD) and iShares Core Dividend Growth ETF (DGRO). VYM differentiates itself by offering broader diversification (holding over 400 stocks) compared to SCHD's roughly 100 holdings. While its 2.26% yield is lower than specialized real estate options like <a href="/o-dividend">Realty Income (O)</a>, its broad market exposure provides crucial insulation against sector-specific downturns.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="faq-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <details>
        <summary>What is the vym dividend?</summary>
        <p>The VYM dividend is a quarterly distribution paid to shareholders, derived from the Vanguard High Dividend Yield ETF's holdings of primarily U.S. companies characterized by higher-than-average dividend yields.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What is the vym dividend yield?</summary>
        <p>Currently, the VYM dividend yield sits at approximately 2.26%, offering a compelling premium over broad market index funds while maintaining a conservative risk profile.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What is the vym dividend history?</summary>
        <p>VYM has a robust dividend history of consistent growth. Annual payouts have grown from $3.10 per share in 2021 to over $3.50 per share in 2025.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What is the projected vym dividend yield 2025?</summary>
        <p>The final VYM dividend yield for 2025 normalized around 2.26%, reflecting steady corporate earnings among value-oriented companies despite shifting interest rates.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What is the forecasted vym dividend yield 2026?</summary>
        <p>While exact figures depend on ongoing market performance and dividend declarations, analysts anticipate the VYM dividend yield in 2026 will maintain a competitive baseline near the 2.5% to 3.0% range assuming stable price appreciation.</p>
      </details>
    </section>
  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
      const calcBtn = document.getElementById('calcBtn');
      if(calcBtn) {
        calcBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
          const shares = parseFloat(document.getElementById('sharesInput').value) || 0;
          const price = parseFloat(document.getElementById('priceInput').value) || 0;
          const yieldPct = 0.0226; // 2.26%

          const principal = shares * price;
          const incomeNoDrip = principal * yieldPct;

          // Simple quarterly compounding approximation for DRIP
          const quarterlyRate = yieldPct / 4;
          const finalValue = principal * Math.pow(1 + quarterlyRate, 4);
          const incomeDrip = finalValue - principal;

          document.getElementById('resNoDrip').textContent = '$' + incomeNoDrip.toLocaleString(undefined, {minimumFractionDigits: 2, maximumFractionDigits: 2});
          document.getElementById('resDrip').textContent = '$' + incomeDrip.toLocaleString(undefined, {minimumFractionDigits: 2, maximumFractionDigits: 2});
          document.getElementById('calcResults').style.display = 'block';
        });
      }
    });
  </script>

  <style is:inline>
    /* NO :root block. Use CSS vars: --bg-color, --card-bg, --border-color, --accent-color, --text-primary, --text-secondary */
    .page-content { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.5rem; }
    .hero { text-align: center; padding: 3rem 0 2rem; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .subtitle { color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 1.1rem; }
    .card { background: var(--card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; margin: 1.5rem 0; }
    table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1.5rem 0; }
    th, td { padding: 0.75rem 1rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color); }
    th { font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 0.85rem; text-transform: uppercase; }
    .faq-section details { margin: 1rem 0; padding: 1rem; background: var(--card-bg); border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); }
    .faq-section summary { font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; }
    .calculator-container label { color: var(--text-primary); }
    a { color: var(--accent-color); text-decoration: none; }
    a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  </style>
</SiteLayout>
